result.execSummary:
The defendant Coral L Monk was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Controlled Substance [Modifiers: Repeater], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: of the Plea and Sentencing Hearing held on June 27, 2016 before the Honorable Neal P. Nettesheim

Reserve Judge Neal Nettesheim presiding for Branch IV:

Cases 16CF10 and 16CM152 called together at 11:17am [mo]
Defendant Coral L Monk in court, in custody with Attorney Karl E Huebner.  ADA Brookellen Teuber appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Constitutional rights reviewed; maximum penalties recited; pleas of " NO CONTEST  " entered on Count #1 of Case 16CF10 and Count #2 of Case 16CM152; factual basis stipulated; the Court accepts the plea, finds Ms. Monk  guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads in and dismisses: all remaining counts 

Sentencing arguments given by Counsel
Statement made by Ms. Monk

On Count #1 of Case 16CF10:
The Court sentences Ms. Monk  to  6  years, with an Initial Term of Confinement in Prison of  3  years, and the maximum time to serve on Extended Supervision of  3 years.  This sentence is to be served concurrent to any sentence in being. 

The Court finds that the Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program "Boot Camp".
The Court finds that the Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.
 

The Court orders as conditions of Extended Supervision:
--to undergo AODA assessment and follow through with treatment recommendations
 per Agent
--to undergo any other assessment, treatment or counseling  as required by the Agent
--
random drug and/or alcohol screening
--make legitimate attempts to obtain/maintain employment and/or education program per Agent
--no possession of controlled substance without valid prescription
--take all prescription medications as prescribed
--no contact with any known drug offender except for treatment purposes as deemed appropriate per Agent
--to comply with DNA sample provision upon demand
--to pay statutory costs


On Count #2 of Case 16CM152: 
The Court sentences Defendant to:
--serve 90  days in Jefferson County Jail; to to served consecutive to the sentence in 16CF10, to be served in Wisconsin State Prison
--pay costs of $243 plus 200 DNA surcharge= $443, to be paid within the extended supervison period of 3 years, non payment shall result to 60 days jail, consecutive


Felony Firearm and Voting-rights prohibitions/warnings given
Explanation of Determinate Sentence form read to Defendant[Court did not complete form]


Days Credit= 4 days in case 16CF10
Days Credit= 0 days in case 16CM152
